WEBVTT

00:01.959 --> 00:05.796
So the other day this guy
in the office asked me...

00:05.963 --> 00:07.215
...what weighs more?

00:07.382 --> 00:10.551
A pound of feathers
or a pound of lead?

00:12.220 --> 00:15.640
-It’s a riddle.
-Yeah, heh, I’ll say it is.

00:16.557 --> 00:21.062
-Adam, they’re both the same.
-Yeah, lead is the same as feathers.

00:22.563 --> 00:25.400
Remind me not to come over
to your place for a pillow fight.

00:27.485 --> 00:29.654
Wow. It was either
come here for breakfast...

00:29.820 --> 00:33.033
...or stay home and figure out
what’s stinking up the fridge.

00:33.199 --> 00:35.326
Hey, Audrey,
back to the pillow fight thing...

00:35.493 --> 00:37.787
...if you and your gal pals
ever need a referee--

00:37.953 --> 00:42.250
All right, I’ll be at home
with my head in the fridge.

00:42.833 --> 00:44.669
You guys wanna hear something
interesting?

00:44.835 --> 00:49.340
Uh, what depends, I can’t take
on another riddle right now.

00:49.882 --> 00:51.301
No, tomorrow’s my anniversary.

00:51.467 --> 00:54.345
-Hey, congrats, man. How many years?
-Sixteen.

00:54.512 --> 00:57.890
Ahh. Ha, if your marriage was a girl
I could date it.

00:59.309 --> 01:00.810
That would be 18.

01:01.727 --> 01:04.314
It is? When did they change that?

01:04.980 --> 01:08.943
And the big thing is,
this year I remembered.

01:10.153 --> 01:11.737
And how did you do that?

01:11.904 --> 01:14.240
Yesterday at work I was spinning
my wedding ring...

01:14.407 --> 01:16.992
...trying to break my record
of 72 seconds...

01:17.827 --> 01:20.580
...when it flew off the desk
and went under the radiator.

01:20.746 --> 01:22.790
Did you break the record?

01:24.584 --> 01:25.668
No.

01:25.835 --> 01:27.545
Oh, God.

01:29.046 --> 01:30.047
Oh.

01:30.215 --> 01:34.885
When I went to go get it, I noticed our
wedding date engraved on the inside.

01:35.636 --> 01:38.389
But I haven’t even told you
the best part.

01:38.556 --> 01:40.891
That I believe.

01:41.058 --> 01:43.311
Usually by this time
Audrey’s dropped a bunch of hints...

01:43.478 --> 01:45.938
...about what she wants
me to get her or what she’d like to do.

01:46.105 --> 01:49.650
But this year? Nothing.
I’m thinking maybe she forgot.

01:50.901 --> 01:53.113
Hey, buddy, I’m really sorry.

01:53.279 --> 01:56.073
Why? It would be the greatest thing
that ever happened.

01:56.241 --> 01:58.243
Better than the time
that squirrel beat up a possum?

01:58.409 --> 01:59.577
[CHUCKLES]

01:59.744 --> 02:03.038
-I don’t believe that happened.
-I know what I saw.

02:04.415 --> 02:06.792
Anyway, why is it great
if she forgot your anniversary?

02:06.959 --> 02:08.169
Because usually I forget.

02:08.336 --> 02:11.131
I’ve been the goat in our marriage
for a long time.

02:11.297 --> 02:13.633
I forget things, I’m selfish,
I’m insensitive.

02:13.799 --> 02:15.551
That’s not gonna change.

02:16.344 --> 02:19.680
But if I remember in the same year
Audrey forgot...

02:19.847 --> 02:21.807
...I totally win.

02:21.974 --> 02:25.478
And more importantly, she loses.

02:25.645 --> 02:26.646
[CHUCKLES]

02:26.812 --> 02:29.649
Oh, I think she lost 16 years ago.

02:32.402 --> 02:33.444
[SEÑOR HAPPY'S
"HOW MANY WAYS" PLAYING]

02:33.611 --> 02:35.780
♪ How many ways
To say I love you ♪

02:38.032 --> 02:41.786
♪ How many ways
To say that I'm not scared ♪

02:42.662 --> 02:47.500
♪ With you by my side
There is no denying ♪

02:47.667 --> 02:50.878
♪ I can't wait for me and you ♪♪

02:56.301 --> 02:58.303
[♪♪♪]

02:59.011 --> 03:03.057
Hey, you would not believe
this Italian girl I met last night.

03:03.224 --> 03:04.850
Why is it you feel the need
to tell me...

03:05.017 --> 03:07.562
...of every woman
into whose pants you gain entry?

03:08.271 --> 03:10.273
I’ve yet to gain entry.

03:10.440 --> 03:13.484
Uh, she doesn’t speak any English.
My Italian’s a little rusty...

03:13.651 --> 03:17.905
...but I will tell you that her pantalones
are muy caliente.

03:18.864 --> 03:19.949
That’s Spanish.

03:20.115 --> 03:22.827
Ah, merci.

03:24.454 --> 03:25.538
French.

03:25.705 --> 03:27.039
See, this is why I need you.

03:27.206 --> 03:30.167
I need you to come along on my date
tomorrow night and be our translator.

03:30.335 --> 03:35.172
And that brings us to the part
of the morning where I ask, why me?

03:35.340 --> 03:37.300
I'm assuming you speak Italian, right?

03:37.467 --> 03:39.134
I mean, you speak Spanish, French...

03:39.302 --> 03:42.222
...and what’s that crazy one you do
on the phone with your mom?

03:42.388 --> 03:44.181
It’s so irritating.

03:44.349 --> 03:48.269
Honestly, this is you asking me
for a favor? I’ll pass.

03:49.395 --> 03:51.146
Well, wait...

03:52.273 --> 03:54.400
...would you pass on this?

03:54.567 --> 03:55.818
[SNIFFS]

03:55.985 --> 03:59.364
Hmm? Smells good.

04:01.115 --> 04:04.535
I wouldn’t even consider this
if I weren't grossly underpaid...

04:04.702 --> 04:06.871
...and in desperate need of cash
to pay off student loans.

04:07.037 --> 04:08.706
No.

04:09.206 --> 04:11.542
Not quite, termite.

04:11.709 --> 04:13.878
You’ll get your money
at the end of the date.

04:14.044 --> 04:17.089
Ah, the policy
for all your romantic encounters.

04:17.757 --> 04:19.759
[♪♪♪]

04:20.843 --> 04:22.512
Hey, what do you wanna do
tomorrow night?

04:22.678 --> 04:24.680
Um, wanna see a movie?

04:24.847 --> 04:27.808
I’ll bring my man-purse,
we can sneak in a bunch of candy.

04:29.018 --> 04:30.978
Not that I’m not turned on by that...

04:31.145 --> 04:33.063
...but I was thinking
we could do something different.

04:33.230 --> 04:34.274
What about bowling?

04:34.440 --> 04:38.027
Um, I don’t think so.

04:38.903 --> 04:41.906
Why not? Weren’t you
like a junior champ or something?

04:42.072 --> 04:45.117
It was All County Junior Men’s
Bowling Champion, division one.

04:45.701 --> 04:49.246
I can’t bowl
in a non-competitive situation.

04:49.789 --> 04:53.626
Well, don’t take it so seriously.
Just relax and have fun.

04:53.793 --> 04:55.795
[CHUCKLING]

04:58.423 --> 05:02.009
Honey, it’s not a switch
I can just turn off, you know.

05:03.678 --> 05:07.557
I have to bowl at the peak level
of my ability, period.

05:09.016 --> 05:12.102
Come on, it would be sexy seeing you
do something you’re great at.

05:12.269 --> 05:14.647
Oh, yeah, you got that right.

05:15.690 --> 05:19.193
Phew, I was pretty popular
with the Alley Cats.

05:19.360 --> 05:22.029
That’s what we call
the bowling groupies.

05:23.072 --> 05:27.034
Yeah, maybe the man purse
full of candy was the way to go.

05:27.201 --> 05:33.207
Too late, you lit the fuse.
Tomorrow night, the Adamizer rolls.

05:35.543 --> 05:37.545
[♪♪♪]

05:39.088 --> 05:41.048
-Okay, thank you, hey.
-Hey.

05:41.215 --> 05:44.719
I just ordered Audrey a huge bouquet
of anniversary flowers.

05:44.885 --> 05:46.887
Oh, she’ll love that.

05:47.054 --> 05:51.642
No, she won’t. Just make her realize
that she forgot, she'll feel like garbage.

05:52.393 --> 05:54.520
I also made
fancy dinner reservations.

05:55.312 --> 05:56.856
Will she love that?

05:58.148 --> 06:00.317
No, she’ll feel too guilty.

06:01.318 --> 06:03.821
This is gonna be great.

06:04.363 --> 06:07.533
Your relationship
is different than mine.

06:07.700 --> 06:08.743
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

06:08.909 --> 06:11.996
Don’t worry, you’ll get there.

06:12.913 --> 06:16.959
Hey, Jeff.
But what if Audrey didn’t forget?

06:18.377 --> 06:21.839
What if she’s just not saying anything
because she’s planning a surprise?

06:22.006 --> 06:23.340
Huh....

06:23.508 --> 06:26.176
She knows I hate surprises...

06:26.636 --> 06:27.803
...so you could be right.

06:28.721 --> 06:30.890
I have to find out
if that’s what she’s up to.

06:31.641 --> 06:34.059
Look, why don’t you just be
a loving husband--

06:34.226 --> 06:35.936
No, no here’s the move.

06:36.103 --> 06:39.398
You come on in with me and you
invite us to do something really lame...

06:39.565 --> 06:40.816
...with you and Jen tomorrow night.

06:40.983 --> 06:42.818
Can’t. Already made plans
to go bowling.

06:42.985 --> 06:43.986
Perfect.

06:44.153 --> 06:46.572
If she accepts,
she clearly has nothing planned.

06:47.239 --> 06:49.575
Okay, fine, but look...

06:49.742 --> 06:52.912
...if you’re gonna bowl with me
you have to play by the rules.

06:53.078 --> 06:55.205
You mean throw the ball
and try to knock down the pins?

06:55.372 --> 06:56.624
[CHUCKLES]

06:56.791 --> 07:00.670
-It’s a little more complicated than that.
-It really isn’t.

07:04.715 --> 07:06.175
-Hey.
-Hey.

07:06.341 --> 07:09.386
-How was work?
-Oh, it was great, you ought to try it.

07:15.893 --> 07:17.562
Oh.

07:18.145 --> 07:19.980
I just had a thought.

07:20.147 --> 07:23.609
Um, Jen and I are going bowling
tomorrow night. You guys wanna come?

07:24.318 --> 07:28.531
Bowling, huh?
What an intriguing offer, uh....

07:30.074 --> 07:31.366
What do you think, Aud?

07:32.034 --> 07:34.078
Sure, yeah.

07:34.704 --> 07:35.955
Let’s go bowling.

07:36.121 --> 07:40.125
It puts us one bird-beak phonograph
away from being the Flintstones.

07:40.292 --> 07:43.921
Well, then tomorrow night,
we shall bowl.

07:44.088 --> 07:47.467
That shall be the activity
of the evening.

07:48.258 --> 07:49.885
Okay.

07:50.052 --> 07:51.721
AUDREY:
What time do you think we should go?

07:56.851 --> 07:59.645
I’m just really excited about bowling.

08:03.566 --> 08:05.568
[♪♪♪]

08:07.695 --> 08:11.782
So, Sophia,
what brought you here from Italy?

08:16.203 --> 08:19.164
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

08:19.331 --> 08:21.333
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

08:25.462 --> 08:27.381
Ahh.

08:30.760 --> 08:32.637
She initially came to visit friends.

08:32.803 --> 08:35.264
But she thinks she’ll stay on
and perhaps take some classes.

08:35.430 --> 08:37.391
Oh, nice.

08:38.601 --> 08:41.896
Well, tell her no need to worry,
she has got all the class in the world.

08:42.062 --> 08:43.313
-I’m not saying that.
-Heh-heh.

08:45.608 --> 08:46.984
Tell her.

08:48.235 --> 08:49.779
[SIGHS]

08:50.112 --> 08:54.033
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

08:54.199 --> 08:55.200
[CHUCKLES]

08:55.367 --> 08:56.619
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

08:57.202 --> 08:59.121
Ah, she liked that one.

08:59.288 --> 09:02.374
I’m sure she was just humoring you
with a fake laugh.

09:02.542 --> 09:06.629
I think I would know
if a woman is faking it.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.591
He said proudly.

09:11.759 --> 09:14.804
-Are you ready to order?
-Oh, very much so.

09:15.262 --> 09:17.682
A gourmet meal is the only
silver lining to this whole ordeal.

09:17.848 --> 09:19.600
Uh, no food for you.

09:19.767 --> 09:23.353
I don’t want you chewing
while you’re translating.

09:23.520 --> 09:26.732
-But, sir--
-No, no, I need your mouth available.

09:28.025 --> 09:29.569
[CHUCKLES]

09:30.027 --> 09:32.947
I need her mouth available too,
heh-heh.

09:34.448 --> 09:35.991
Tell her.

09:38.994 --> 09:40.663
Tell her!

09:46.627 --> 09:49.129
So did they deliver the flowers
to Audrey?

09:49.296 --> 09:51.340
Oh, I, uh, cancelled them.

09:51.506 --> 09:52.883
Why?

09:53.050 --> 09:55.427
I realized they would’ve reminded hers
that she forgot.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.888
So she could run out to get a gift...

09:58.055 --> 10:01.558
...claimed she knew all along,
and stolen my glory.

10:02.602 --> 10:04.729
Heh, that's good thinking.

10:04.895 --> 10:08.691
I also printed out confirmations
of the dinner reservation and flowers...

10:08.858 --> 10:12.903
...so that I have evidence
that I remembered.

10:13.821 --> 10:16.156
You guys are all set, lanes four,
ten, and 12.

10:16.323 --> 10:19.159
Excuse me,
do you have 10 pound balls?

10:20.745 --> 10:22.329
Yes.

10:24.999 --> 10:28.085
Quick question, when was the last time
you washed your balls?

10:30.295 --> 10:34.091
-The balls get washed once a week.
-Interesting.

10:37.511 --> 10:39.179
I gotta go do some visualizing.

10:41.098 --> 10:45.560
Oh, one more question
do you have blue balls?

10:46.729 --> 10:48.480
[♪♪♪]

10:48.689 --> 10:51.066
Sir, Sophia is in the ladies room,
for God’s sake...

10:51.233 --> 10:53.443
...may I please
have a piece of bread?

10:55.487 --> 10:57.657
-Fine. Go quick.
-Ah.

10:59.199 --> 11:00.534
Here she comes.

11:01.160 --> 11:03.078
Ah. Ha-ha-ha

11:03.620 --> 11:05.122
Aloha.

11:05.289 --> 11:08.458
Hey, um, tell her how worldly I am...

11:08.625 --> 11:12.046
...and that I’ve travelled
Europe expensively.

11:13.756 --> 11:18.302
-I assume you mean extensively.
-No, expensively.

11:18.468 --> 11:20.429
I want her to know how loaded I am.

11:21.263 --> 11:23.766
She already knows
that from when you had me tell her...

11:23.933 --> 11:26.852
...you wanted to name
one of your boats after her.

11:27.352 --> 11:29.980
And, sir, you can do better than that.

11:30.147 --> 11:33.233
What am I suppose to name all my boats
after her? The whole fleet?

11:34.443 --> 11:36.987
You have no boats.

11:39.114 --> 11:43.744
I’m saying you should be open
and honest and let her know
what’s in your heart.

11:43.911 --> 11:46.831
All right, take it easy
Timminy Cricket.

11:47.998 --> 11:49.959
Okay, tell her...

11:51.210 --> 11:54.379
-...I’d like to know...
-Okay.

11:54.546 --> 11:57.591
...what color her underpants are.

11:57.758 --> 11:59.343
[CHUCKLES]

12:01.303 --> 12:02.888
No.

12:03.388 --> 12:05.015
Oh, because she’s European...

12:05.182 --> 12:08.060
...she might not be wearing any,
I got you. Okay, okay.

12:09.269 --> 12:11.188
-Good night.
-No, no, no, stay.

12:11.355 --> 12:12.522
Okay, I’m sorry.

12:13.648 --> 12:15.525
All right.

12:16.026 --> 12:17.694
Tell her I’m glad I met her...

12:17.862 --> 12:22.407
...and maybe she'd like to tell me
about her family in Italy?

12:23.951 --> 12:25.285
Now there you go, sir.

12:25.452 --> 12:29.039
-Honest, simple, from the heart.
-All right, just tell her.

12:29.206 --> 12:30.415
[CLEARS THROAT]

12:31.458 --> 12:34.211
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

12:38.173 --> 12:41.635
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

12:44.054 --> 12:45.597
Well?

12:47.099 --> 12:48.517
Um....

12:49.184 --> 12:52.146
She was hoping to pursue
a purely physical relationship.

12:52.312 --> 12:53.480
[CHUCKLES]

12:53.814 --> 12:56.025
Ahh. Ahh.

12:56.733 --> 12:59.778
Pants, one. Heart, zero, all right.

12:59.945 --> 13:02.697
[IN ITALIAN ACCENT]
Physical, heh.

13:03.032 --> 13:04.449
[♪♪♪]

13:05.450 --> 13:07.536
Audrey, are you enjoying
this evening...

13:07.702 --> 13:10.622
...which is distinguished solely
by the fact we went bowling?

13:11.040 --> 13:13.583
Uh, yeah, so far, so good.

13:15.210 --> 13:16.211
Ah.

13:16.545 --> 13:19.423
Aw, you and Jen each have your own
bowling balls?

13:19.589 --> 13:22.176
No, they’re both mine.
One's a spare ball.

13:22.342 --> 13:25.220
-All right, I’ll just use that.
-No, no, no.

13:26.221 --> 13:28.348
It’s not an extra ball,
it’s a ball for spares.

13:28.515 --> 13:30.350
The other one is for strikes.

13:31.143 --> 13:32.436
You gotta be kidding me.

13:32.895 --> 13:36.315
Have you never been
to a sanctioned bowling event?

13:38.775 --> 13:40.319
This should be really fun.

13:43.238 --> 13:45.240
[IN UNISON]
Mmm.

13:46.450 --> 13:47.742
Ah.

13:50.245 --> 13:52.873
Ask Sophia if she’d like
to come back to my place.

13:53.040 --> 13:55.667
Fine, I hope she can hear
over the sound of my stomach...

13:55.834 --> 13:56.919
...eating its own lining.

13:57.669 --> 13:59.629
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

14:00.380 --> 14:01.548
Si.

14:06.345 --> 14:07.888
Yes, she’s ready.

14:08.263 --> 14:10.140
Ohh. Okay.

14:10.307 --> 14:12.935
Done my dirty work here. It is done.

14:13.102 --> 14:14.644
[GIBBERING]

14:16.480 --> 14:18.648
Oh, you’re not done.

14:18.899 --> 14:20.234
[♪♪♪]

14:20.609 --> 14:22.027
Si.

14:22.527 --> 14:24.321
-Yes.
-Mm-hm.

14:24.613 --> 14:26.198
Oh, si.

14:26.656 --> 14:28.033
Yes.

14:28.993 --> 14:30.494
Oh, si.

14:32.121 --> 14:33.705
Oh, yes.

14:34.206 --> 14:35.374
[♪♪♪]

14:35.540 --> 14:37.376
Yes, yes!

14:38.878 --> 14:42.965
Oh, Adam, I accidentally took your
turn when you went to the bathroom.
But, um, you can take mine.

14:43.132 --> 14:47.844
Great, I’d be happy
to add to your 37.

14:48.803 --> 14:50.639
-Um, sorry.
ADAM: No problem.

14:50.805 --> 14:55.102
I was working on a turkey,
but thanks for the two pin contribution.

14:55.269 --> 14:58.022
Hey, why don’t, uh, we take a break?

14:58.188 --> 15:00.315
We’ll have a little time out
and I’ll go get us some drinks.

15:00.482 --> 15:02.276
Oh, I’ll help.

15:04.236 --> 15:07.531
Okay. Audrey’s said nothing
about our anniversary...

15:07.697 --> 15:11.076
...and it’s too late for her to throw
anything together. It’s go time.

15:11.243 --> 15:13.787
-All right, what are you gonna do?
-When she comes back...

15:13.954 --> 15:15.080
...I’ll grab a ball...

15:15.872 --> 15:18.875
-...and a roll strike.
-Not with that follow through.

15:19.043 --> 15:23.172
Then I’ll turn around
and I'm gonna say happy anniversary.

15:23.338 --> 15:26.050
This will be my shining moment
as a husband.

15:26.216 --> 15:29.761
My moment of triumph.

15:29.929 --> 15:32.056
-Happy anniversary.
-What the....

15:32.514 --> 15:34.016
Happy anniversary, honey.

15:34.183 --> 15:35.517
-You remembered?
AUDREY: Of course.

15:35.684 --> 15:38.938
What, just now? You ran and grabbed
the bowling alley cake?

15:39.104 --> 15:40.730
Heh, no.

15:40.897 --> 15:43.984
This cake is from that bakery
that you love on 72nd Street.

15:44.526 --> 15:47.279
And I know you’ve had a lot to deal
with this year with me....

15:47.446 --> 15:50.032
...quitting my job and finding
a surrogate and all that nonsense.

15:50.199 --> 15:55.996
And I didn’t want to put any more
pressure on you. So it’s okay
that you forgot again, I’m not upset.

15:56.163 --> 15:59.874
No, this year I didn’t forget.
I remembered.

16:00.542 --> 16:05.005
Okay, Jeff, you don’t have to do that.
I told you I am not upset.

16:05.172 --> 16:06.840
-No, really I remembered.
ADAM: Yeah.

16:07.007 --> 16:09.259
Yeah, he’s got proof.
Show her the receipts.

16:09.426 --> 16:10.719
No.

16:11.220 --> 16:13.805
-What receipts?
-There are no receipts. I, uh....

16:14.723 --> 16:16.475
I forgot.

16:16.641 --> 16:18.852
-They're right there in his pocket.
-No, they’re not.

16:22.439 --> 16:23.940
AUDREY:
Oh.

16:24.108 --> 16:27.319
A dinner reservation
and a receipt from the florist.

16:27.486 --> 16:30.655
So why am I not at this restaurant
smelling these flowers?

16:31.365 --> 16:33.700
You’re not focusing
on the right thing here.

16:34.409 --> 16:35.410
The point is...

16:37.371 --> 16:39.123
...I remembered.

16:41.458 --> 16:43.543
And you thought I forgot.

16:44.669 --> 16:45.670
So you....

16:46.380 --> 16:48.423
You canceled the dinner
and the flowers...

16:48.590 --> 16:51.593
...but retained the confirmations
to shove in my face.

16:52.886 --> 16:55.055
Happy anniversary.

17:00.060 --> 17:02.312
I don't want you
hanging around with him anymore.

17:06.775 --> 17:08.485
Now can we get back to bowling?

17:11.030 --> 17:13.032
[♪♪♪]

17:19.329 --> 17:20.580
Hey.

17:22.916 --> 17:25.085
I got you these.

17:27.962 --> 17:29.673
You still mad?

17:30.549 --> 17:34.928
You mean, from the worst thing you've
ever done that happened 20 minutes ago?

17:35.637 --> 17:38.307
Still raw. I hear you.

17:40.142 --> 17:42.811
These flowers are just temporary...

17:42.977 --> 17:45.480
...and not just
because they're mostly dead.

17:46.690 --> 17:49.609
I reordered you
the giant bouquet flowers.

17:49.776 --> 17:52.404
And we have those dinner reservations
for tomorrow night.

17:54.114 --> 17:56.783
Well, that's a start.

17:56.950 --> 17:59.744
You have your choice
of 5:15 or 10:45.

18:03.248 --> 18:04.708
You know...

18:04.874 --> 18:08.295
...if you spend a fraction of the time
you spend game playing...

18:08.462 --> 18:10.964
...and plotting against me
toward nice things--

18:11.131 --> 18:14.050
I won't deny it, this one kind of
got away from me.

18:15.677 --> 18:19.098
I, uh, I'm really sorry.

18:19.264 --> 18:23.185
I gotta get to the gym.
I'm tense, I've been tense.

18:24.436 --> 18:25.604
[SIGHS]

18:25.770 --> 18:27.814
I know you have.

18:27.981 --> 18:30.817
I was just so proud of myself
when I remembered.

18:30.984 --> 18:35.155
Well, at least that shows you
were trying to be a good husband.

18:35.697 --> 18:39.033
-Then when I thought you forgot--
-You got greedy.

18:40.535 --> 18:41.536
I did.

18:43.079 --> 18:44.831
I flew too close to the sun.

18:47.167 --> 18:52.131
Well, to use a phrase I've used
far too often on our anniversary...

18:53.423 --> 18:54.883
...I forgive you.

18:55.634 --> 18:57.927
-You do?
-Yeah, come on.

18:58.094 --> 19:01.723
We're 16 years in,
nobody's going anywhere.

19:03.975 --> 19:05.602
[CHUCKLES]

19:05.769 --> 19:06.770
Oh.

19:06.936 --> 19:09.148
Who'd have thought
you remembering our anniversary...

19:09.314 --> 19:12.609
...would be so much worse
than you forgetting it?

19:13.610 --> 19:16.070
Well, don't worry.
That won't happen again.

19:16.238 --> 19:18.198
[CHUCKLES]

19:18.365 --> 19:22.411
You know, Audrey,
sometimes I don't think I deserve you.

19:23.119 --> 19:25.539
So there are times
when you think you do?

19:27.123 --> 19:28.542
[CHUCKLES]

19:32.921 --> 19:34.506
[♪♪♪]

19:37.717 --> 19:39.261
Timmy.

19:40.304 --> 19:42.806
Timmy. I need you.

19:44.308 --> 19:47.727
Oh. Again? Sir, at a certain point
I really don't think...

19:47.894 --> 19:50.605
-...this is about the translating.
-No, no, no.

19:51.356 --> 19:53.858
You gotta help me eject her
from the cockpit.

19:54.025 --> 19:59.573
At some point during the night
she got a little clingy and annoying.

20:02.367 --> 20:03.618
Well, you know sir...

20:03.785 --> 20:07.038
...that's your problem because
my translating duties are over.

20:07.206 --> 20:11.125
Oh, that's funny because
my paying you duties are over. Wha--?

20:11.293 --> 20:13.212
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

20:13.378 --> 20:14.754
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

20:16.256 --> 20:18.132
All right, tell her, uh...

20:18.300 --> 20:22.387
...you know, I had fun
but we both know the score.

20:25.849 --> 20:27.392
Fine.

20:29.811 --> 20:32.105
[IN ITALIAN]

20:38.362 --> 20:43.074
Uh, you know, I wish her the best
but I got to move on.

20:44.951 --> 20:46.411
[IN ENGLISH]
Okay.

20:47.912 --> 20:50.790
[IN ITALIAN]

20:54.503 --> 20:56.255
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

20:57.506 --> 21:00.884
Uh, she's taking it
like a real trooper, ha, ha.

21:03.553 --> 21:06.515
[♪♪♪]

21:09.726 --> 21:11.728
[♪♪♪]
